<plot>Susan keeps vigil over her husband Ben, terminally ill, lying in a hospital bed. He's on life support, unconscious. She considers ending those supports. She looks through a scrapbook and remembers the day they met, how they courted, and other intimate moments. She holds a compass, the first keepsake he gave her after pulling her out of harm's way at a busy New York street corner. Has she made up her mind?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?033159</url></doc>
